\fs29\fsmilli14667 Sentimentalism may be defined many ways, but Burns\'92s letter highlights one of them: the longing after an imagined world, sometimes but not necessarily utopian or feminocentric, in which sympathy, benevolence, and goodness are the predominant virtues. 
